                                <li>The value investing process, both fact and fiction. The financial markets have a long and distinguished history of implementing value investment techniques. People generally credit Benjamin Graham and David Dodd as the originators of this style of value investing, which involved acquiring undervalued productive assets. People often trace this habit back to the twentieth century. Value investing has been considered an essential component of the landscape of equity investment for the majority of the last century.</li>
